Rook Ceph Kubernetes Cheat Sheet
1. Cluster Status
kubectl get cephcluster -A

Detailed:

kubectl -n rook-ceph describe cephcluster rook-ceph

Ceph health:

kubectl -n rook-ceph exec -it deploy/rook-ceph-tools -- ceph status
kubectl -n rook-ceph exec -it deploy/rook-ceph-tools -- ceph health detail
Rook Ceph Pods

List all Rook pods:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods -o wide

Watch:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods -w

Check OSD pods:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep osd

Check MON:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep mon

Check MGR:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep mgr
Ceph Toolbox

Enter toolbox:

kubectl -n rook-ceph exec -it deploy/rook-ceph-tools -- bash

Exit:

exit
Ceph Commands (inside toolbox)
Overall status
ceph -s

or

ceph status
Health
ceph health
ceph health detail
Cluster FSID
ceph fsid
Monitors
ceph mon stat
Managers
ceph mgr stat
OSD Management

List OSDs:

ceph osd tree

OSD status:

ceph osd status

OSD utilization:

ceph osd df

Show OSD metadata:

ceph osd metadata

Check OSD count:

ceph osd ls

Restart OSD pod:

kubectl -n rook-ceph delete pod rook-ceph-osd-<id>

Example:

kubectl -n rook-ceph delete pod rook-ceph-osd-0
Pools

List pools:

ceph osd pool ls

Pool details:

ceph osd pool ls detail

Pool usage:

ceph df
RBD Commands

List images:

rbd ls -p replicapool

Show image info:

rbd info -p replicapool <image-name>

List snapshots:

rbd snap ls -p replicapool <image-name>
Kubernetes Storage
Storage Classes

List:

kubectl get storageclass

Details:

kubectl describe storageclass rook-ceph-block
PVC

List PVC:

kubectl get pvc -A

Details:

kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name>

List PV:

kubectl get pv
CSI Troubleshooting

Check CSI pods:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep csi

RBD CSI logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs \
deploy/csi-rbdplugin-provisioner \
-c csi-provisioner

Node plugin logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs \
daemonset/csi-rbdplugin \
-c csi-node-driver-registrar
OSD Provisioning Troubleshooting

Check prepare jobs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get jobs

Logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs \
job/rook-ceph-osd-prepare-<node-name>

Example:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs \
job/rook-ceph-osd-prepare-kube-worker1

Delete failed prepare jobs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph delete job \
rook-ceph-osd-prepare-<node>
Device Discovery

Check Ceph devices:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get cephcluster rook-ceph -o yaml

On worker nodes:

lsblk

Check disks:

fdisk -l

Check signatures:

blkid /dev/sdb

Clear old Ceph data:

⚠️ DESTROYS DATA

dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdb bs=100M status=progress
sync
Ceph Logs

Operator logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs deploy/rook-ceph-operator

OSD logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs rook-ceph-osd-0

MON logs:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs rook-ceph-mon-a
Restart Rook Components

Restart operator:

kubectl -n rook-ceph rollout restart deploy rook-ceph-operator

Restart CSI:

kubectl -n rook-ceph rollout restart deploy csi-rbdplugin-provisioner

Restart all Ceph pods:

kubectl -n rook-ceph delete pod --all

(Kubernetes recreates them automatically.)

Node / Disk Expansion

Check Ceph cluster:

ceph osd tree

Add new disk:

Attach disk to worker
Verify:
lsblk
Let Rook discover:
kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep prepare
Useful Kubernetes Commands

Events:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get events --sort-by=.lastTimestamp

All resources:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get all

Storage objects:

kubectl get sc,pv,pvc -A
Emergency Checks

Ceph not healthy:

ceph -s
ceph health detail
ceph osd tree
ceph df

PVC stuck Pending:

kubectl describe pvc <name>

Check CSI:

kubectl -n rook-ceph get pods | grep csi

OSD not creating:

kubectl -n rook-ceph logs job/rook-ceph-osd-prepare-<node>
